<TITLE>Calvin Alley</TITLE>
<TEXT>Calvin Lowrey Alley began life on earth Sept. 6, 1949, in Little Rock, departing Jan. 27, 2017. Calvin was a retired furniture designer and manufacturer and a member of First Presbyterian Church in Fort Smith. Calvin enjoyed hunting, fishing, creating and building things, but most of all, boating on Lake Ouachita. He graduated from Northside [m1] High School in Fort Smith in 1967, where he was involved in numerous clubs and activities, including president of the Key Club and a delegate for Boys State. Calvin graduated from Kendall College of Art and Design of Grand Rapids, Mich., in 1973 with a bachelors degree in furniture design. He immediately put his degree to use with employment at J. Gordon Perlmutter Associates in Piscataway, N.J. Upon returning to Fort Smith, he worked for Garrison Furniture, Southland Furniture, Kay Chair, Baldwin Piano and Kawai Corp. He ended his working career by teaching woodworking at Northside High School. 
 
Calvin is survived by his wife, Marilyn L Alley of 31 years; sons, Christopher L. Alley and girlfriend Jennifer Forrest, Duayne S. Alley and girlfriend, Rhiana Keiser, Charles J. Alley and wife, Michele Alley; his mother, Johnnie B. Alley; sister, Trude A. Moore and husband Dennis; numerous cousins, nieces, nephews and other family members, as well as many longtime friends. Calvin is predeceased by his father, Charles Pinckney Alley; and his brother, Gary Lee Alley. 
 
The family wishes to say thank you to all the friends for their prayers and foods. We especially want to thank Heather Montgomery for her loving care of Calvin in his last days. 
 
Memorial service will be held at First Presbyterian Church in Fort Smith onTuesday at 2 p.m. Family will greet friends following the service in the parlor of the church. In lieu of flowers, the family requests memorials to Northside High School Class of 1967, c/o Dixie Geren, 413 N. 53rd Street, Fort Smith, AR 72903, or Fountain of Youth Adult Daycare Center, 2801 McKinley Avenue, Fort Smith, AR 72908. Cremation is under the direction of McConnell Funeral Home. 
 
Please visit www.mcconnellfh.com to sign online guestbook.</TEXT>
